Hi,

Johnson Controls is now a defendant in S.D. Fla., facing a patent infringement complaint filed by Innovation Sciences, LLC on June 11, 2026. The plaintiff's profile fits a familiar NPE pattern: a licensing-focused entity with little or no operating business, asserting the asserted patents as leverage toward settlement.

In cases like Innovation Sciences, LLC v. Johnson Controls International PLC, the defendant's best early move is usually a credible invalidity position. Stilta can run a targeted prior-art search against the asserted patents and produce structured claim-chart analysis quickly, giving your team the foundation it needs to evaluate IPR or PTAB options before the litigation schedule tightens.

If it would be useful, we are happy to send a brief overview of how Stilta approaches NPE invalidity work. A short call works too, whatever fits your team's bandwidth right now.

